OL,3,CGovernment face vote on controversial
OL,4,Ctwo-child benefit cap
OL,6,FThe new Labour government is facing
OL,7,Fthe threat of its first backbench
OL,8,Frevolt, as MPs prepare to vote on the
OL,9,Fcontroversial two-child benefit cap.
OL,11,FKeir Starmer has been under mounting
OL,12,Fpressure to scrap the policy, which
OL,13,Frestricts child welfare payments to
OL,14,Fthe first two children born in most
OL,15,Ffamilies with some exceptions.
OL,17,FThe prime minister and his cabinet say
OL,18,Fthe state of the public finances means
OL,19,Fthey cannot afford to abolish the
OL,20,Fbenefit limit without economic growth.
